00150 #define M_WIMS_SIZE_BIT         1
00151 #define M_WIMS_SIZE_CHAR        8
00152 #define M_WIMS_SIZE_SHORT       16
00153 #define M_WIMS_SIZE_INT         16
00154 #define M_WIMS_SIZE_LONG        16
00155 #define M_WIMS_SIZE_LLONG       32
00156 #define M_WIMS_SIZE_FLOAT       -1
00157 #define M_WIMS_SIZE_DOUBLE      -1
00158 #define M_WIMS_SIZE_POINTER     ((M_model == M_WIMS_16) ? 16 : 32)
00159 #define M_WIMS_SIZE_UNION       -1
00160 #define M_WIMS_SIZE_STRUCT      -1
00161 #define M_WIMS_SIZE_BLOCK       -1
00162 #define M_WIMS_SIZE_MAX         ((M_model == M_WIMS_16) ? 16 : 32)

00179 int M_wims_type_size(int mtype)
00180 {
00181     switch (mtype) {
00182         case M_TYPE_VOID:               return M_WIMS_SIZE_VOID;
00183         case M_TYPE_BIT_LONG:           return M_WIMS_SIZE_BIT;
00184         case M_TYPE_BIT_LLONG:          return M_WIMS_SIZE_BIT;
00185         case M_TYPE_BIT_SHORT:          return M_WIMS_SIZE_BIT;
00186         case M_TYPE_BIT_CHAR:           return M_WIMS_SIZE_BIT;
00187         case M_TYPE_CHAR:               return M_WIMS_SIZE_CHAR;
00188         case M_TYPE_SHORT:              return M_WIMS_SIZE_SHORT;
00189         case M_TYPE_INT:                return M_WIMS_SIZE_INT;
00190         case M_TYPE_LONG:               return M_WIMS_SIZE_LONG;
00191         case M_TYPE_LLONG:              return M_WIMS_SIZE_LLONG;
00192         case M_TYPE_FLOAT:              return M_WIMS_SIZE_FLOAT;
00193         case M_TYPE_DOUBLE:             return M_WIMS_SIZE_DOUBLE;
00194         case M_TYPE_POINTER:            return M_WIMS_SIZE_POINTER;
00195         case M_TYPE_UNION:              return M_WIMS_SIZE_UNION;
00196         case M_TYPE_STRUCT:             return M_WIMS_SIZE_STRUCT;
00197         case M_TYPE_BLOCK:              return M_WIMS_SIZE_BLOCK;
00198         default:
00199             return -1;
00200     }
00201 }

00203 int M_wims_type_align(int mtype)
00204 {
00205     switch (mtype) {
00206         case M_TYPE_VOID:               return M_WIMS_ALIGN_VOID;
00207         case M_TYPE_BIT_LONG:           return M_WIMS_ALIGN_BIT;
00208         case M_TYPE_BIT_LLONG:          return M_WIMS_ALIGN_BIT;
00209         case M_TYPE_BIT_SHORT:          return M_WIMS_ALIGN_BIT;
00210         case M_TYPE_BIT_CHAR:           return M_WIMS_ALIGN_BIT;
00211         case M_TYPE_CHAR:               return M_WIMS_ALIGN_CHAR;
00212         case M_TYPE_SHORT:              return M_WIMS_ALIGN_SHORT;
00213         case M_TYPE_INT:                return M_WIMS_ALIGN_INT;
00214         case M_TYPE_LONG:               return M_WIMS_ALIGN_LONG;
00215         case M_TYPE_LLONG:              return M_WIMS_ALIGN_LLONG;
00216         case M_TYPE_FLOAT:              return M_WIMS_ALIGN_FLOAT;
00217         case M_TYPE_DOUBLE:             return M_WIMS_ALIGN_DOUBLE;
00218         case M_TYPE_POINTER:            return M_WIMS_ALIGN_POINTER;
00219         case M_TYPE_UNION:              return M_WIMS_ALIGN_UNION;
00220         case M_TYPE_STRUCT:             return M_WIMS_ALIGN_STRUCT;
00221         case M_TYPE_BLOCK:              return M_WIMS_ALIGN_BLOCK;
00222         default:
00223             return -1;
00224     }

00227 void M_wims_char(M_Type type, int unsign)
00228 {
00229     type->type = M_TYPE_CHAR;
00230     type->unsign = unsign;

00276 void M_set_model_wims(char *model_name)
00277 {
00278     if (!strcasecmp(model_name, "16") )
00279         M_model = M_WIMS_16;
00280     else if (!strcasecmp(model_name, "24") )
00281         M_model = M_WIMS_24;
00282     else
00283         M_assert (0, "M_set_model_wims:  Illegal model specified!");
00284 }
